<paragraph blockId="12.[151,558,1364,1390]" box="[151,558,1364,1390]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,558,1364,1390]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,558,1364,1390]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Daniel" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[207,380,1364,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klapperichi">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[207,380,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">N. klapperichi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="413" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1434,1639]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1434,1459]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The coloration and the pattern are similar to those of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="van Eecke" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[980,1138,1436,1459]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sumatrana">
<emphasis box="[980,1138,1436,1459]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">N. sumatrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group. The male genitalia of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Daniel" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[329,490,1470,1495]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klapperichi">
<emphasis box="[329,490,1470,1495]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">N. klapperichi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group are similar to those of the 
<taxonomicName box="[959,1081,1471,1495]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="effracta">
<emphasis box="[959,1081,1471,1495]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">N. effracta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group, but differ in the narrower distal section of the costa, the significantly narrower apical process of the costa, the presence of the distal membranous lobe of valva, and the presence of one or several denticles on the ventral margin of the ampulla. The female genitalia of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Daniel" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[413,573,1578,1603]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klapperichi">
<emphasis box="[413,573,1578,1603]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">N. klapperichi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group are characterized in the presence of the subostial lobes of the ductus bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
